defaultThe courts in the UK are already conversant with EU law and with decisions of the Strasbourg court.
default              
defaultApart from the position under the 
defaultdevolution 
defaultActs
default, 
defaultUK
default courts and legislators have no experience of prior review of proposed legislation.  One disadvantage is that political opponents of a Bill may turn their opposition into a legal attack on the Bill, 
defaultby
default seeking political support from the courts.  Prospective review of this kind is necessarily abstract
default, and the common law tradition has had little experience of 
defaultit
default.  In some contexts, for example if the constitution were to establish a formal system of federalism, it might be appropriate for a question as to t
